2. Introduction
In today’s digital world, strong passwords are essential to protect personal and professional data. However, many people still use weak passwords that are easy to guess or crack.
This project, Password Generator Using Python, is a desktop-based application developed using the Tkinter library. It helps users generate strong, random, and secure passwords instantly using a simple and user-friendly graphical interface.
The main aim of this project is to make secure password creation easy and accessible for everyone, even non-technical users.
________________________________________
3. Problem Statement
Many users:
•	Use weak passwords (like names, birthdates, “123456”, etc.)
•	Reuse passwords for multiple accounts
•	Don’t know how to create strong passwords
This makes them vulnerable to hacking, brute-force attacks, and data theft.
Problem:
How to provide users with an easy-to-use application to generate strong random passwords without manual effort?
Solution:
A GUI-based Python application that automatically generates secure and random passwords based on user-selected length.
________________________________________
4. Functional Requirements
The system should be able to:
1.	Allow the user to select the password length.
2.	Generate a random and secure password.
3.	Display the generated password on screen.
4.	Allow the user to copy the password to clipboard.
5.	Generate multiple passwords at once (5 or 10).
6.	Display multiple passwords in a separate text area.
7.	Show messages like “Password Copied” for user feedback.
________________________________________
5. Non-Functional Requirements
1.	Usability:
Easy for anyone to use without technical knowledge.
2.	Performance:
Password generation should be fast and instantaneous.
3.	Portability:
Should run on Windows, Linux, and macOS.
4.	Security:
The app should not store passwords permanently.
5.	Reliability:
The program should not crash during normal operations.
________________________________________
6. System Architecture
The architecture of the system is simple and standalone:
User → Tkinter GUI → Password Generator Logic → Display Result
Main Components:
•	User Interface (Tkinter)
•	Password Generation Logic
•	Clipboard Module
•	Display Module
